<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Yahoo! devotes issue to music, Net
 &HT;    By Charles Hadaad
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Internet is becoming an increasingly big part in both the
marketing and distribution of music. Read what rocker David Bowie
has to say about music and the Internet in the April issue of
Yahoo! Internet Life. Says Bowie of the Net, ``This is for real. It
will change everything that we know _ absolutely everything.''
</P>
<P>
   Bowie is just one element in Yahoo!'s April issue, which is
devoted to music and the Internet. Other articles include a look at
the war between the music industry and a group of upstarts trying
to set the standard for how music is distributed through the Net.
Many music publishers and distributors think the Net will forever
change the way you buy recordings, because it is fast and it also
does something marketers like _ encourages impulse buying.
</P>
<P>
   On CD-ROM
</P>
<P>
   Tonka cars, the favorite of many a kid, have gone digital. The
company now offers a computer CD version of its cars. In ``Tonka
Garage,'' kids can build their own cars and crash them. You can
also convert images of cars to trading cards, decals and other
things that can be printed out.
</P>
<P>
   A companion game, ``Tonka Raceway,'' lets you create racetracks
and then race the cars you've created. Or you can pick cars and
trucks to race from a list of 30 already created for the game.
Published by Hasbro Interactive, these games are available only for
PCs running Windows 95 or a higher version of the operating system.
</P>
<P>
   Online
</P>
<P>
   Need help with your taxes? Now you can turn to the Web for
everything from advice to forms. Some sites provide information on
the latest changes in the tax code. Others let you print out
worksheets to help calculate your return. Still others let you fill
out and file your return electronically.
</P>
<P>
   Here are a couple of sites worth check out. Start with Deloitte
&AMP; Touche Online at www
</P>
<P>
   .dtonline.com, then cruise to ABCNews.com at www.abcnews
</P>
<P>
   .go.com/sections/business
</P>
<P>
   .taxes98. Finally, if you want to do your taxes online, take a
look at Turbotax.com at www
</P>
<P>
   .turbotax.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
