</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Questions, questions, questions
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   So, you're the Curious George type. Always asking why, why, why?
</P>
<P>
   If you're ``Itching to Know'' things about space, then Lanacane
and the National Space Society can help. Kids in kindergarten
through the sixth grade can send space questions to
www.lanacane.com/contest.html. The 10 best questions will be
answered by NASA astronauts, and winners will receive prizes.
</P>
<P>
   One of the 10 winners will be selected to take a three-day trip
to U.S. Space Camp. All questions will be answered.
</P>
