<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NEWS FOR KIDS: U.S. attacks Yugoslavia
 &HT;    By Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The United States and its allies began bombing Yugoslavia last
week, trying to bring peace to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   Kosovo is a province that wants independence from Yugoslavia.
Yugoslavia's Serbian leaders don't want to let it break away, and
Serbian military forces have killed or driven away many Kosovo
residents.
</P>
<P>
   North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) warplanes and missiles
blasted targets, trying to weaken the Serbian military and its
defense systems.
</P>
<P>
   NATO officials insist the bombing won't stop until Serb leaders
agree to a peace deal.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   Students witness
</P>
<P>
   historic baseball game
</P>
<P>
   One hundred American students traveled to Cuba to watch the
Baltimore Orioles take on the Cuban National team over the weekend.
The students also got to play their own game against Cuban kids.
</P>
<P>
   ``The kids here play a more exciting kind of baseball,'' said
Jimmy Petrila, a 12-year-old from Washington. ``In the United
States, people swing for the fences. Here there are a lot of bunts
and stealing. It is a more strategic kind of playing.''
</P>
<P>
   The students, all from the Baltimore-Washington area, were among
a small group of foreigners who got to watch the exhibition match
in person.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first time in 40 years that a major-league team
played in Cuba. Big leaguers used to travel to the island nation
before the 1959 revolution that brought Communist Fidel Castro to
power.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE
</P>
<P>
   Poacher busted by DNA
</P>
<P>
   For the first time, Florida wildlife officials used a deer's DNA
to prove the animal was killed illegally. DNA is a substance found
in all living creatures.
</P>
<P>
   The hunter in the case said he had killed a buck, or male deer.
But when the deer meat was analyzed by researchers at the
University of Florida, they proved it was from two does _ female
deer. It is illegal to kill does in certain areas.
</P>
<P>
   The hunter was fined $1,661, and his hunting license was
suspended for three years.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
