<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NEWS FOR KIDS: Wrestling goes Hollywood
 &HT;    By Jeffry Scott
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Hollywood is seeking new action heroes to star in its movies,
and guess where it's looking?
</P>
<P>
   Producers and directors are glued to wrestling shows, like TNT's
``WCW Monday Nitro'' and the USA Network's ``Raw Is War'' to find
their new stars.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hollywood Hogan'' has led the way from the ring to the silver
screen, acting in more than 13 films, including ``No Holds
Barred,'' ``Mr. Nanny,'' and ``Rocky III.''
</P>
<P>
   Now other famous guys in shorts _ Stone Cold Steve Austin, Bill
Goldberg and Kevin Nash _ hope to be box office smashes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Producers are looking for new action stars now that Sylvester
Stallone and Arnold Schwarzenegger are getting older,'' says
Hollywood agent Barry Bloom, who works for WCW star Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   Goldberg stars as a bad guy named Romeo in a new action movie,
``Universal Soldier, The Sequel,'' which will be in movie theaters
this summer.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm always reading new movie scripts,'' says the 6-foot,
4-inch-tall, 291-pound Goldberg, who has become one of the hottest
wrestlers around.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's what I really want to do, be in the movies,'' Goldberg
says.
</P>
<P>
   The rivalry between the wrestlers even extends outside the ring.
The WCW's Goldberg _ who has challenged WWF's big star, Stone Cold
Steve Austin to a $100,000 grudge match _ beat out Austin for the
role in ``Universal Soldier.''
</P>
<P>
   Austin has appeared in a recent episode of the TV show, ``Nash
Bridges,'' playing a cop, and the producers say they want him in
another.
</P>
<P>
   The WCW's Kevin Nash (``Big Sexy'') appeared on an episode of
``The Love Boat'' with Goldberg last September.
</P>
<P>
   In that show, Nash played Goldberg's wrestling partner who
wouldn't leave Goldberg alone, even though Goldberg was on his
honeymoon.
</P>
<P>
   That's kind of funny since Nash was suddenly Goldberg's worst
enemy in December. He beat him to become WCW world heavyweight
champion.
</P>
<P>
   Goldberg vows: ``I'll be back!''
</P>
<P>
   That is, if he's not too busy making a movie!
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
