 &UR; By COREY S. POWELL &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   The era of big, unmanned space missions is over. NASA learns to
think big by building small but powerful explorers that are the
stuff of science-fiction novels _ robots that could fit on a spoon,
solar sails and rockets no larger than a computer chip. Corey S.
Powell is Discover magazine's Senior Editor, Online.
</P>
