<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NEWTOYS-TEX </SLUG>
 
FIVE NEW ELECTRONIC LEARNING AIDS (ELAs) FROM 1999 TOY FAIR 
(Accompanies BC-KIDSTOYS) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   _ Hug &AMP; Learn Baby Tad plush frog, 6-24 months, (Leap Frog, $25,
August). With a push on the toy's electronic bib, Baby Tad recites
shapes such as triangles, squares or circles. Instills both shape
and color recognition.
</P>
<P>
   _ Goodnight Blue talking storybook, 18 months and up
(Fisher-Price/Mattel, $35, August). Enhances reading skills.
``Blue'' of ``Blue Clues'' totes an electronic storybook. As the
parent reads the book, the child can press a button and the book's
character will say a phrase. The plush Blue's eyes close slowly as
each page is turned.
</P>
<P>
   _ Pooh Smart Sticks, 2 years and up (Tiger Electronics, $10 and
up, available now). Using Pooh character voices, this toy teaches
colors, shapes, body parts, word/image association, vocabulary and
more. Several models available.
</P>
<P>
   _ Smart Start Little Smarty Cat mini-laptop, 4 years and up
(VTech, $20, in the fall). In a portable, laptoplike design, a
friendly voice quizzes children on the alphabet and simple
mathematics.
</P>
<P>
   _ GeoSafari Talking Globe Traveler mini-quizzer, 8 years and up
(Educational Insights, $49, now available). Hand-held, portable
version of the award-winning GeoSafari Talking Globe. Quizzes one
or two players on geography-related questions.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
