</P>
<P>
   A pregnant teen-ager finds help and
</P>
<P>
   caring in a small Oklahoma town.
</P>
<P>
   12. BLACK AND BLUE, by Anna Quindlen. (Dell, $7.50.)
</P>
<P>
   After her husband turns violent, a woman flees to
</P>
<P>
   Florida with her son to start a new life.
</P>
<P>
   13.(x) THE COFFIN DANCER, by Jeffrey Deaver. (Pocket, $6.99.)
</P>
<P>
   A quadriplegic police detective and his protege hunt a serial
</P>
<P>
   killer in New York.
</P>
<P>
   14. THE DEEP END OF THE OCEAN, by Jacquelyn Mitchard.
</P>
<P>
   (Signet, $7.99.) The disappearance of a 3-year-old boy
</P>
<P>
   brings anguish and redemption.
</P>
<P>
   15.(x) JEWEL, by Bret Lott. (Washington Square/Pocket, $14.)
</P>
<P>
   The life of a poor Mississippi woman is strained
</P>
<P>
   and enriched by her daughter, who has Down syndrome.
</P>
<P>
   16.(x) THE NOTEBOOK, by Nicholas Sparks. (Warner Vision, $5.99.)
</P>
<P>
   A veteran meets an old flame.
