 &HT;    I call upon the Yugoslav government to accept the political part
of the agreement worked out in Paris and to discuss a mechanism for
its implementation that would involve the participation of the
international community. Russia could play a major constructive
role in this process, whose resumption is indispensable if we are
not to slip into another Cold War.
 c.1999 La Stampa  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Mikhail Gorbachev, the last leader of the Soviet Union before
its collapse in 1991 and Nobel Peace Prize winner, now heads the
