by Kevorkian's murder conviction, which they say clears away a
distraction that confused the issue. By Pam Belluck.
</P>
<P>
   NY-DIALLO-PROTESTS (New York) _ Monday is to be the last day of
protests in front the NYC Police headquarters on the fatal shooting
by police of the unarmed African immigrant Amadou Diallo in
February.
