BBO-YOUTH-PITCHERS (Los Angeles) _ Column exploring the issue of
youth baseball coaches overusing the arms of their most talented
pitchers. These kids are so good that they can simply dominate
their opponents, tempting coaches to use them as much as possible.
Even with inning-limit rules that most leagues have, these kids can
be overused. How much does a youth coach owe a player who may have
a professional future, like a Kerry Woods _ the Chicago Cubs phenom
who recently blew out his arm and won't be back for a year or two
if at all. 
