STEVENS REPLACES McCARRON 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA, Calif. _ Santa Anita Derby week began Monday with a
switch of Hall of Fame jockeys as trainer Bob Baffert said Gary
Stevens will replace Chris McCarron aboard General Challenge in
Saturday's $750,000 race.
</P>
<P>
   Stevens was scheduled to be in Arkansas on Saturday to ride 1998
Kentucky Derby winner Real Quiet in the Oaklawn Handicap. But
Baffert withdrew Real Quiet from that race, citing dissatisfaction
with the colt's 122-pound assignment, three pounds more than Puerto
Madero.
</P>
<P>
   That decision freed Stevens, who is Baffert's No.1 jockey, to
ride in the Santa Anita Derby, which he has won six times.
</P>
<P>
   That move left McCarron, who has won the West's top Kentucky
Derby prep twice, without a mount. It seemed likely he would get
the long-vacant riding assignment on Baffert-trained Finder's Gold.
</P>
<P>
   Baffert's three Santa Anita Derby horses had 6-furlong workouts
Monday morning. General Challenge was clocked in 1:10, Prime Timber
in 1:11 3/5, Finder's Gold in 1:13.
</P>
<P>
   Prime Timber, the leading contender for the May 1 Kentucky
Derby, will be ridden again by David Flores. Also expected for the
1[-mile Santa Anita race: Desert Hero (Corey Nakatani), Capsized
(Alex Solis) and Honest Lady (Kent Desormeaux).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-29-99 1933EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
