<SLUG> BC-BY-DESIGN-FASHION-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THROWING MULES A CURVE
</HEADLINE>
  (fb) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Last spring's shoe was the mule or slide; as flat as a bedroom
slipper. This year, the mule has been feminized with a curvy
mid-high heel to wear with skirts and with cropped or long pants.
</P>
<P>
   Manolo Blahnik's sleek pointy-toe versions come in lizard in a
range of colors ($615 at Bergdorf Goodman) or in floral linen ($455
at Barneys New York). Bergdorf's also has private label mules in
pale pink patent ($168), Diego Dolcini's clear plastic mules with
leather toe caps ($295) and Sigerson Morrison's open-toed beige
mules ($195). Barneys has Michel Perry's patent mules in coral,
black or white ($350); Costume National's black or white leather
($285), and Andrea Pfister's evening style in black or white
spattered with rhinestones ($560).
</P>
<P>
   Warren Edwards has leather or suede mules in many colors as well
as in perforated leopard-print or pearlized patent ($455).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
