branch of science traditionally dominated by men: physics. But most
of all, she is known as the scientist who slowed light down to a
walk. Perfectly at home with such subjects as quantum mechanics,
Hilbert spaces and Bose-Einstein condensates, Dr. Hau, at 39, is
rapidly reaching the top of her profession, her colleagues agree.
(Rick Friedman/New York Times Photo)
